00:17:38,113 --> 00:17:41,283
I'm confused. We got the badges.
We got the guns.

244
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:43,326
You got a screwdriver.

245
00:17:43,577 --> 00:17:46,329
It's kind of like takin' a screwdriver
to a gunfight.

246
00:17:46,413 --> 00:17:48,498
And "pig," that's an old phrase.

247
00:17:48,582 --> 00:17:52,919
Y'all must not be from around here.
Y'all must be from another country...

248
00:17:53,837 --> 00:17:55,839
Drop the guns. Please.

249
00:17:56,089 --> 00:17:59,176
This is a police matter.
It's got nothin' to do with you.

250
00:17:59,259 --> 00:18:00,760
Drop the guns.

251
00:18:03,597 --> 00:18:06,349
Think we're gonna have to do this
the hard way.

252
00:18:07,225 --> 00:18:08,727
I can't fight, man.

253
00:18:08,977 --> 00:18:12,689
What do you mean you can't fight?
It's a fine time to tell me now.

254
00:18:12,772 --> 00:18:14,733
Get down on your knees. Now.

255
00:18:15,192 --> 00:18:17,402
He likes you, that's the good news.

256
00:18:18,028 --> 00:18:20,405
Sorry. Not without dinner and a movie.

257
00:18:27,329 --> 00:18:30,957
Your friend likes to do things the hard way.
Now, how about you?

258
00:18:31,124 --> 00:18:35,170
My friend, he's a little bit country,
I'm a little bit rock-n'-roll.

259
00:18:35,253 --> 00:18:36,546
What does that mean?

260
00:18:36,630 --> 00:18:39,341
Just an expression. What do you want?

261
00:18:39,758 --> 00:18:41,176
You...dead.

262
00:18:42,385 --> 00:18:43,261
Why?

263
00:18:43,428 --> 00:18:45,263
Because the pay is so good.

264
00:18:47,807 --> 00:18:50,060
How about if I double the pay?

265
00:18:51,895 --> 00:18:55,565
You have balls. But I don't think
you have enough money.

266
00:18:56,191 --> 00:18:57,359
Well, I do.

267
00:18:57,567 --> 00:18:59,611
I got thousands of dollars in my pocket.

268
00:18:59,694 --> 00:19:03,156
I'm gonna reach into my back pocket
slowly to get my wallet.

269
00:19:03,281 --> 00:19:04,991
I have a lot of cash...

270
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,244
or you could take plastic.

271
00:19:07,452 --> 00:19:08,578
"Plastic?"

272
00:19:08,995 --> 00:19:10,580
This is rock-n'-roll.

273
00:19:52,873 --> 00:19:55,625
For a minute I forgot you said
you can't fight.

274
00:19:55,709 --> 00:19:57,002
It's not that I can't fight.

275
00:19:57,085 --> 00:19:59,629
I'm not supposed to.
It's against my religion.

276
00:19:59,713 --> 00:20:01,214
- Great.
- I'm a Buddhist.

277
00:20:01,298 --> 00:20:03,341
Yeah. You're a Kung Fu priest.

278
00:20:06,428 --> 00:20:07,888
Who sent you, man?

279
00:20:08,722 --> 00:20:10,265
The Russian Mafia.

280
00:20:14,060 --> 00:20:15,645
- Let me try.
- You speak Russian?

281
00:20:15,729 --> 00:20:16,980
A little bit.

282
00:20:18,106 --> 00:20:22,110
Answer me, goddamn it, before I beat
the shit out of you, you dumb ass!

283
00:20:23,862 --> 00:20:26,740
- You speak good Russian.
- Yes. Black Russian.

284
00:20:27,449 --> 00:20:30,785
Read him his rights even though
he's a little unconscious.

285
00:20:34,581 --> 00:20:35,790
He knows 'em.

286
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:39,419
I'm tellin' you, Captain, this guy is weird.

287
00:20:39,503 --> 00:20:40,921
Yeah, show me a cop who isn't.

288
00:20:41,004 --> 00:20:43,673
Look, I'm not talkin' about a cop
who wears pantyhose.

289
00:20:43,757 --> 00:20:47,344
This guy, he speaks Chinese,
he dresses like a monk...

290
00:20:47,928 --> 00:20:52,057
and the Russians yesterday, he took
those guys out like Bruce Lee, only better.

291
00:20:52,140 --> 00:20:55,435
I mean, I saw him use his credit card
like a goddamn Ginsu knife.

292
00:20:55,519 --> 00:20:57,020
Where would you learn that?

293
00:20:57,103 --> 00:20:58,522
I don't know, maybe the Army.

294
00:20:58,605 --> 00:21:01,608
What do you want me to do, Jim,
look at his resume?

295
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:05,529
Don't come to me with this kind of shit.
Just work with the guy.

296
00:21:09,825 --> 00:21:11,368
"Work with the guy".

297
00:22:01,710 --> 00:22:03,128
What does this say to you?

298
00:22:03,211 --> 00:22:05,297
Punishment and purification.

299
00:22:06,882 --> 00:22:10,677
He believes he's helping these people
by turnin' them into martyrs.

300
00:22:10,927 --> 00:22:13,513
Only he can't get any satisfaction.

301
00:22:13,597 --> 00:22:15,807
So he keeps doin' it,
gettin' bolder and bolder...

302
00:22:15,891 --> 00:22:18,268
until he's either caught or killed.

303
00:22:18,643 --> 00:22:21,688
And he ain't gettin' his orders
from the Devil, either.

304
00:22:21,771 --> 00:22:24,107
He believes he's listenin' to Jesus himself.

305
00:22:24,191 --> 00:22:26,109
You learn well, Grasshopper.

306
00:22:30,113 --> 00:22:31,656
Task force, Campbell.

307
00:22:36,828 --> 00:22:37,996
All right.

308
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:42,876
Two more bodies.

309
00:23:08,443 --> 00:23:09,528
Hey, slow down.

310
00:23:09,611 --> 00:23:12,155
It's all right, man, we'll be back later.

311
00:23:25,210 --> 00:23:27,879
Hey, man, get this virgin
off the crime scene.

312
00:23:53,864 --> 00:23:56,449
We got Andrew Dunleavy, a psychiatrist.

313
00:23:56,533 --> 00:23:59,035
This is his wife Ellen.
There are two children...

314
00:23:59,119 --> 00:24:00,912
but we haven't been able to locate them.

315
00:24:00,996 --> 00:24:03,039
Roden, squash that, man.

316
00:24:04,332 --> 00:24:06,084
Are you all right, Jack?

317
00:24:24,019 --> 00:24:25,937
- Jim, you got a minute?
- Sure.

318
00:24:26,021 --> 00:24:29,024
Careful, he wants to borrow money.
I know that look.

319
00:24:29,107 --> 00:24:32,277
- Got somethin' for you to look at.
- What is it?

320
00:24:32,903 --> 00:24:36,198
Found a print at the Dunleavy scene,
on the woman's body.

321
00:24:36,281 --> 00:24:38,283
Beautiful. It's about time.

322
00:24:38,783 --> 00:24:41,328
- Let's run it right away.
- Already did.

323
00:24:42,287 --> 00:24:43,497
It's Cole's.

324
00:24:55,300 --> 00:24:58,178
Your brother still works
for Intelligence, right?

325
00:25:00,055 --> 00:25:02,807
Tell him to find out everything he can
on Cole.

326
00:25:03,016 --> 00:25:04,476
Off the record.

327
00:25:09,064 --> 00:25:11,942
We'll extend the house-to-house canvas
by four blocks.

328
00:25:12,025 --> 00:25:15,862
We're lookin' for any links
between the victims. Where they shop...

329
00:25:15,987 --> 00:25:18,865
get their cars repaired,
pictures developed...

330
00:25:18,949 --> 00:25:20,826
anything, no matter how small.

331
00:25:20,909 --> 00:25:24,412
Do me a favor and get me copies
of these blood paintings on the walls...

332
00:25:24,496 --> 00:25:26,289
in this stack of crime-scene photos.

333
00:25:26,373 --> 00:25:29,584
Send 'em out to every psych ward
and prison throughout the US.

334
00:25:29,668 --> 00:25:31,378
Maybe a former patient.

335
00:25:31,711 --> 00:25:33,880
I don't know, I just think that...

336
00:25:34,047 --> 00:25:37,509
this work is so unique that any prisoner,
psychiatrist or priest...

337
00:25:37,592 --> 00:25:39,135
would definitely not forget it.

338
00:25:39,219 --> 00:25:41,263
All right, everybody knows what to do.

339
00:25:41,346 --> 00:25:42,430
Let's go.

340
00:26:00,407 --> 00:26:01,825
No, I understand.

341
00:26:03,326 --> 00:26:05,412
I'll get there as fast as I can.

342
00:26:07,539 --> 00:26:08,540
Thanks.

343
00:26:08,623 --> 00:26:10,333
Hey, you're home early.

344
00:26:11,877 --> 00:26:13,003
What's up?

345
00:26:13,753 --> 00:26:18,258
I have a new patient. They don't think
she has a long time to live, so....

346
00:26:22,470 --> 00:26:23,972
What's wrong?

347
00:26:24,222 --> 00:26:26,183
There's been another killing.

348
00:26:28,059 --> 00:26:29,227
Same guy?

349
00:26:31,271 --> 00:26:32,189
Yeah.

350
00:26:32,314 --> 00:26:33,690
I'm sorry, Jack.

351
00:26:36,026 --> 00:26:38,111
He killed Ellen and her husband.

352
00:26:38,278 --> 00:26:39,487
He did what?

353
00:26:41,198 --> 00:26:44,534
I gotta go tell my kids
that their mother is dead.

354
00:26:46,453 --> 00:26:47,913
Jesus, Jack!

355
00:26:49,789 --> 00:26:52,375
I think he's makin' it personal, you know?

356
00:27:30,705 --> 00:27:32,374
Westlake Security.

357
00:27:34,209 --> 00:27:38,129
I'd like you to tell Mr. Smith
that Mr. Jones needs to contact him...

358
00:27:38,755 --> 00:27:40,298
right away.

359
00:27:56,857 --> 00:27:58,900
I think there may be a problem.

360
00:27:59,651 --> 00:28:01,111
Spit it out, son.

361
00:28:03,446 --> 00:28:05,991
Mr. Jones, he's asking to see you.

362
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,160
Really?

363
00:28:08,952 --> 00:28:10,996
I wonder what took him so long?

364
00:28:11,246 --> 00:28:13,206
What would you like me to do?

365
00:28:15,041 --> 00:28:16,459
lgnore him.

366
00:28:17,294 --> 00:28:18,962
He's being dealt with.

367
00:28:19,212 --> 00:28:21,590
And we have bigger fish to fry.

368
00:28:22,257 --> 00:28:23,675
Whatever you say.

369
00:28:31,725 --> 00:28:34,227
"Ten Ways To Spend Your Weekend".

370
00:28:52,954 --> 00:28:55,123
This is all we could get on Cole.

371
00:28:57,751 --> 00:28:58,877
Let's see.

372
00:29:00,128 --> 00:29:03,882
NYPD, Homicide, Task Force Command
on the DeMarco serial killings.

373
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:07,886
Lots of medals, good cop.

374
00:29:09,012 --> 00:29:11,181
He tracked down the DeMarco killer...

375
00:29:11,264 --> 00:29:13,141
shot him on a rooftop, one-on-one...

376
00:29:13,225 --> 00:29:16,228
and then was busted for actin'
without sanction.

377
00:29:16,353 --> 00:29:18,271
Two coffees, Raffi. Extra sugar.

378
00:29:18,355 --> 00:29:20,774
- No coffee for me.
- They're both for me.

379
00:29:21,358 --> 00:29:22,609
Anything else?

380
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:25,445
Nothin' in the military records.

381
00:29:25,946 --> 00:29:29,533
Almost nothin' before the NYPD.
Looks like this guy came out of nowhere.

382
00:29:29,616 --> 00:29:32,452
Are you tellin' me we don't know nothin'
about this guy?

383
00:29:32,536 --> 00:29:34,955
Yeah, there's one thing we know for sure.

384
00:29:35,038 --> 00:29:37,666
He used to be married
to the Dunleavy woman.

385
00:29:39,501 --> 00:29:40,794
Son of a bitch.

386
00:29:41,962 --> 00:29:46,091
"In my Father's house,
there are many rooms. If it were not so...

387
00:29:46,508 --> 00:29:50,303
"...would I have told you that I go
to prepare a place for you?

388
00:29:51,054 --> 00:29:54,641
"Thomas said to him, 'Lord,
we do not know where you are going.'

389
00:29:54,808 --> 00:29:57,310
"Jesus said to him, 'I am the way...'

390
00:29:57,644 --> 00:30:01,982
"...and the truth and the life,
no one comes to the Father, but by me".

391
00:30:13,577 --> 00:30:16,413
Why didn't you tell anybody
it was your ex-wife?

392
00:30:16,830 --> 00:30:19,624
You know they would have pulled me
off the case.

393
00:30:19,708 --> 00:30:21,918
You should've told me.
We're workin' together.

394
00:30:22,002 --> 00:30:23,295
Well, I didn't.

395
00:30:24,546 --> 00:30:28,300
We lD'd the couple at the motel.
Eugene and Sonya Roslov.

396
00:30:28,592 --> 00:30:30,510
Russian, just like you said.

397
00:30:31,011 --> 00:30:32,679
Any connection to the others?

398
00:30:32,762 --> 00:30:34,931
No. They weren't even Catholic.

399
00:30:35,432 --> 00:30:37,767
There goes that theory. What's next?

400
00:30:40,395 --> 00:30:41,938
This is empty.

401
00:30:42,272 --> 00:30:44,524
It's everything we know about you.

402
00:30:44,608 --> 00:30:46,943
Your background's nothin' but smoke
and mirrors.

403
00:30:47,027 --> 00:30:47,944
Who are you, Jack?

404
00:30:48,028 --> 00:30:49,362
I can't get into it right now.

405
00:30:49,446 --> 00:30:51,239
Yeah, well maybe you can get into this.

406
00:30:51,323 --> 00:30:53,950
We found your print
at your ex-wife's house.

407
00:30:55,827 --> 00:30:58,747
She was my ex-wife.
I pick up my kids there all the time.

408
00:30:58,830 --> 00:31:00,540
The print's on the body.

409
00:31:02,083 --> 00:31:03,293
Planted.

410
00:31:03,460 --> 00:31:05,962
And there's a puff of smoke
comin' from the grassy knoll.

411
00:31:06,046 --> 00:31:08,715
What kind of bullshit
you tryin' to run, man?

412
00:31:09,716 --> 00:31:13,303
I ain't always been a cop.
That's all I can tell you right now.

413
00:31:14,971 --> 00:31:17,599
You are one mysterious motherfucker.

414
00:31:18,892 --> 00:31:21,186
Nobody seems to know anything
about your past...

415
00:31:21,269 --> 00:31:24,272
and the only evidence I got
points right at you.

416
00:31:24,356 --> 00:31:26,733
Now, does that worry you, Jack?

417
00:31:28,068 --> 00:31:29,528
Do I look worried?

418
00:31:29,945 --> 00:31:31,947
Well, it damn sure worries me.

419
00:31:55,011 --> 00:31:56,513
Hello, Lento's.

420
00:31:57,097 --> 00:31:59,015
No, I'm sorry, we're closed.

421
00:32:00,392 --> 00:32:02,769
- No. It's a private lunch.
- Excuse me.

422
00:32:02,894 --> 00:32:04,688
There is nothing I can do.

423
00:32:06,314 --> 00:32:09,025
I'm telling you we're closed today.
Tomorrow we'll be open.

424
00:32:09,109 --> 00:32:11,194
It'll be fine. Come then. It'll be a nice...

425
00:32:11,278 --> 00:32:12,779
Excuse me a minute.

426
00:32:12,988 --> 00:32:15,657
Asshole, what are you blind?
We're closed!

427
00:32:15,740 --> 00:32:17,868
You kind of talk too much!

428
00:32:19,661 --> 00:32:22,747
Yeah, go ahead, come on over,
we'll give you a table.

429
00:32:37,679 --> 00:32:40,473
You're unbelievable.
What are you doing here?

430
00:32:40,557 --> 00:32:44,102
You need to turn around and leave.
That's what you need to do.

431
00:32:50,859 --> 00:32:54,404
You don't call, you don't write.
What's worse, you don't take my calls.

432
00:32:54,488 --> 00:32:57,365
Excuse me. Excuse me, sir...Senator....

433
00:32:59,784 --> 00:33:03,246
Why don't you and I take your
little sensitive ponytail...

434
00:33:03,330 --> 00:33:06,625
and your little sissy beads,
and get out of here, okay?

435
00:33:11,505 --> 00:33:13,006
As I was saying....

436
00:33:14,049 --> 00:33:17,636
Senator, as you can see,
some urgent business has just come up.

437
00:33:18,553 --> 00:33:20,472
Thank you, Senator, so kind.

438
00:33:25,227 --> 00:33:29,689
It's been such a long time, Jack.
That's the name you're using now, correct?

439
00:33:29,773 --> 00:33:31,024
At the moment.

440
00:33:32,067 --> 00:33:35,070
Can I get you a bite to eat?
The food is truly wonderful...

441
00:33:35,153 --> 00:33:37,197
although the service leaves a little
to be desired.

442
00:33:37,280 --> 00:33:40,826
Cut the shit. I need some names,
names of consultants.

443
00:33:41,326 --> 00:33:44,955
Don't tell me there's a problem
you can't take care of yourself?

444
00:33:45,330 --> 00:33:48,208
It's about the serial killings.
I know you know about them.

445
00:33:48,291 --> 00:33:51,419
Yes, I do. Truly wicked. Sorry about Ellen.

446
00:33:53,588 --> 00:33:54,965
Wonderful woman.

447
00:33:56,633 --> 00:33:59,970
You know, the last two murders
were definitely the work of a pro...

448
00:34:00,053 --> 00:34:01,972
not a serial killer.

449
00:34:02,138 --> 00:34:05,767
And I just have the feeling
that you might know who this pro is.

450
00:34:06,768 --> 00:34:08,562
Well, let me guess.

451
00:34:09,855 --> 00:34:11,731
They've discovered your checkered past...

452
00:34:11,815 --> 00:34:14,067
and now they suspect you.

453
00:34:14,734 --> 00:34:16,153
Not exactly.

454
00:34:16,319 --> 00:34:20,448
They're still not totally up on my past yet,
but I know you are.

455
00:34:21,825 --> 00:34:25,120
Therefore, I'm sure you realize
what I'm capable of doing to you...

456
00:34:25,203 --> 00:34:26,663
if I have to.

457
00:34:28,331 --> 00:34:30,083
Yes, indeed, I do.

458
00:34:30,167 --> 00:34:32,294
What kind of consultant you lookin' for?

459
00:34:32,377 --> 00:34:36,173
This individual gives me the impression
that he's a freelancer.

460
00:34:36,464 --> 00:34:39,467
Hiding his targets in the scenario
of a serial killer.

461
00:34:39,551 --> 00:34:41,845
Likes a .22, likes head shots.

462
00:34:42,596 --> 00:34:46,224
Seems to be inflicting costume wounds
on the victims after they're dead...

463
00:34:46,308 --> 00:34:48,727
and has excellent cleaning skills.

464
00:34:49,144 --> 00:34:51,813
I'll certainly keep my eyes peeled,
and my ears open.

465
00:34:51,897 --> 00:34:54,733
Right now, that's just not
gonna be good enough.

466
00:34:55,025 --> 00:34:58,236
Jack, you know there's a problem.
I'm kind of busy right now...

467
00:34:58,320 --> 00:35:00,071
testifying before Congress.

468
00:35:00,155 --> 00:35:04,493
They're getting kind of cranky
about where we get our core-op funds...

469
00:35:04,993 --> 00:35:06,828
but, as it's you...

470
00:35:08,330 --> 00:35:10,582
I'll certainly do the best I can.

471
00:35:10,999 --> 00:35:12,542
For old times' sake.

472
00:35:15,504 --> 00:35:17,214
Good to see you, buddy.

473
00:35:18,715 --> 00:35:19,883
Bye, buddy.

474
00:35:26,014 --> 00:35:29,351
If you ever pull that shit with me again,
I'll kill you.

475
00:35:29,434 --> 00:35:33,605
All your little Chinese, moo-shoo pork
potions will not save you next time.

476
00:35:34,105 --> 00:35:36,441
You shouldn't knock Chinese potions.

477
00:35:36,525 --> 00:35:38,527
I have something in my pocket right now...

478
00:35:38,610 --> 00:35:41,488
that'll completely clear up that bruise
on your forehead.

479
00:35:41,571 --> 00:35:42,614
What bruise?

480
00:35:42,697 --> 00:35:43,907
That bruise.

481
00:36:47,179 --> 00:36:48,889
Do you validate parking?

482
00:36:56,396 --> 00:36:57,689
Hello, Lento's.

483
00:36:58,315 --> 00:37:02,652
No, no, no, that' won't work.
We're closed for renovation. I'd say...

484
00:37:04,654 --> 00:37:06,907
two months. Yeah. Thanks.

485
00:37:11,203 --> 00:37:12,871
You're chasing your tail with this one.

486
00:37:12,954 --> 00:37:17,167
He probably bought it at a flea market.
No way we're gonna find him there.

487
00:37:17,792 --> 00:37:21,880
We're gonna have to go back to basics.
You guys gotta do your canvassing.

488
