00:55:24,171 --> 00:55:27,549
He was a brilliant soldier.
West Point, that kind of thing.

736
00:55:28,300 --> 00:55:32,554
I found him in Vietnam.
Recruited him for a special projects unit.

737
00:55:33,847 --> 00:55:35,807
The Program, we called it.

738
00:55:35,974 --> 00:55:38,602
He handled a lot of odd jobs for us.

739
00:55:39,352 --> 00:55:41,354
- Such as?
- Now, Mr. Deverell...

740
00:55:41,646 --> 00:55:44,399
don't ask about things
you don't really want to know.

741
00:55:44,483 --> 00:55:47,319
Suffice to say, to the people he hunted
for us...

742
00:55:47,402 --> 00:55:50,071
he was known as "The Glimmer Man".

743
00:55:51,323 --> 00:55:53,450
There'd be nothing but jungle...

744
00:55:54,367 --> 00:55:55,952
then a glimmer...

745
00:55:57,913 --> 00:55:59,539
then you'd be dead.

746
00:56:00,165 --> 00:56:02,417
Why isn't he still with you?

747
00:56:02,667 --> 00:56:06,505
He was booted out of the program in '84.
Went native on us.

748
00:56:08,423 --> 00:56:10,342
Made up his own assignments.

749
00:56:10,509 --> 00:56:12,511
Disappeared...for months.

750
00:56:12,886 --> 00:56:14,888
Ended up in Thailand...

751
00:56:15,764 --> 00:56:18,308
chanting in some temple or other.

752
00:56:19,059 --> 00:56:21,686
They say he was saved by a holy man.

753
00:56:23,188 --> 00:56:27,400
So many stories about this fella,
I don't know which ones are true anymore.

754
00:56:33,490 --> 00:56:35,700
- What do we do about him?
- Broom him.

755
00:56:36,535 --> 00:56:39,454
Time to lose everybody
who knows anythin'.

756
00:56:41,665 --> 00:56:43,542
And I mean everybody.

757
00:56:45,460 --> 00:56:46,962
Johnny's no threat.

758
00:56:48,296 --> 00:56:51,758
I beg to differ. He's already spilled
to the shrink.

759
00:56:53,510 --> 00:56:56,513
The poor boy knows too much.
Simple as that.

760
00:56:57,931 --> 00:56:59,558
Johnny'll do what I say.

761
00:56:59,641 --> 00:57:01,893
Let me put this another way.

762
00:57:02,310 --> 00:57:05,105
I have four loose links in this operation:

763
00:57:05,397 --> 00:57:07,566
Two cops, you, and the boy.

764
00:57:08,608 --> 00:57:10,318
Three of you have to go.

765
00:57:10,569 --> 00:57:12,404
You can choose which three.

766
00:57:15,615 --> 00:57:17,868
You'll have to do it yourself.

767
00:57:18,410 --> 00:57:19,953
Frank, I'll take care of Johnny.

768
00:57:20,036 --> 00:57:22,622
Who's gonna take care of Cole
and Campbell?

769
00:57:22,789 --> 00:57:25,125
I'll put Donald on the others right away.

770
00:57:25,208 --> 00:57:26,793
That's the spirit.

771
00:57:26,960 --> 00:57:29,546
Now, come on in. The water's fine.

772
00:59:54,191 --> 00:59:55,192
Shit!

773
01:00:45,492 --> 01:00:47,494
Take the kids upstairs.

774
01:00:54,084 --> 01:00:55,752
- John Cole?
- Yes.

775
01:00:56,002 --> 01:00:58,380
Miller and Russo from Internal Affairs.

776
01:00:58,463 --> 01:01:00,632
We have a warrant for your arrest.

777
01:01:01,049 --> 01:01:03,802
Do you want to take a minute
to gather a few things?

778
01:01:03,885 --> 01:01:06,721
No, that's perfectly all right.
I'm ready to go.

779
01:01:58,398 --> 01:02:00,650
Coldest winter I can remember in LA.

780
01:02:01,443 --> 01:02:02,903
Wettest, too.

781
01:04:04,483 --> 01:04:06,067
They got you, too.

782
01:04:06,151 --> 01:04:08,778
No, I bought all this shit after the riots.

783
01:04:08,945 --> 01:04:11,406
It means we're close, man, we're close.

784
01:04:11,573 --> 01:04:13,366
Do I look like I give a shit?

785
01:04:13,450 --> 01:04:17,662
You better give a shit, 'cause they ain't
gonna stop till they get us both.

786
01:04:22,083 --> 01:04:24,002
Does this say, "deer antler"?

787
01:04:25,086 --> 01:04:26,588
Give me that.

788
01:04:27,672 --> 01:04:31,009
- It was a free sample.
- There's a whole case over here.

789
01:04:31,092 --> 01:04:33,094
Just stay out of my shit.

790
01:04:33,595 --> 01:04:37,307
Can I just take this moment to tell you
how moved I am deeply?

791
01:04:37,474 --> 01:04:39,643
Yeah, well, that makes one of us.

792
01:04:40,435 --> 01:04:43,063
I found somethin'
on your ex-wife's phone records.

793
01:04:43,146 --> 01:04:45,482
Someone called the house the night
she was killed.

794
01:04:45,565 --> 01:04:49,903
They called six times, only talked about 10
or 15 seconds each time.

795
01:04:50,487 --> 01:04:52,489
You got a number or somethin'?

796
01:04:53,240 --> 01:04:57,035
Could I take those CDs?
They look like I could still use them.

797
01:04:57,994 --> 01:04:59,454
Got it. Come on.

798
01:04:59,621 --> 01:05:02,707
Could I ask you somethin'?
Did you actually live in this shitbox?

799
01:05:02,791 --> 01:05:04,417
Man, will you come on?

800
01:05:25,313 --> 01:05:27,774
Now, what if this is really our guy?

801
01:05:27,941 --> 01:05:29,943
- We'll reason with him.
- Right.

802
01:05:33,822 --> 01:05:35,073
- What?
- Police!

803
01:05:38,076 --> 01:05:39,703
I'm Detective Cole,
this is Detective Campbell...

804
01:05:39,786 --> 01:05:42,372
with the Los Angeles Police Department.

805
01:05:42,455 --> 01:05:44,791
We'd like to ask you some questions
about some calls...

806
01:05:44,875 --> 01:05:47,294
you may have made to a Dr. Dunleavy.

807
01:05:50,839 --> 01:05:53,341
You look like you just came from a riot.

808
01:05:53,592 --> 01:05:54,384
Thanks.

809
01:05:54,467 --> 01:05:56,928
He looks like he just came from a riot.

810
01:05:57,345 --> 01:06:00,891
Yeah, this number's billed to me,
but it's my daughter's phone.

811
01:06:04,561 --> 01:06:06,396
I know you, don't I?

812
01:06:07,397 --> 01:06:10,692
Yeah, you know me. You put my boyfriend
through a window.

813
01:06:12,652 --> 01:06:15,363
High school, window. I remember now.

814
01:06:15,989 --> 01:06:18,617
You're Johnny Deverell's girlfriend,
aren't you?

815
01:06:18,700 --> 01:06:19,451
So?

816
01:06:19,534 --> 01:06:23,622
So, I was just wondering, how long
have you known Dr. Dunleavy?

817
01:06:24,915 --> 01:06:27,042
I don't know any Dunleavy.

818
01:06:27,792 --> 01:06:30,587
You called him the night he was killed.

819
01:06:31,296 --> 01:06:34,174
Yeah. Well, it wasn't me.
I don't need a shrink.

820
01:06:35,133 --> 01:06:37,135
We never said he was a shrink.

821
01:06:40,305 --> 01:06:43,099
Okay, I knew him but I didn't call him.

822
01:06:43,975 --> 01:06:45,393
I wonder who did?

823
01:06:46,937 --> 01:06:48,104
Johnny did.

824
01:06:48,688 --> 01:06:51,691
When he got busted with the coke,
they made him see a shrink.

825
01:06:51,775 --> 01:06:53,819
The shrink was Dunleavy, right?

826
01:06:54,152 --> 01:06:55,153
Millie.

827
01:06:55,570 --> 01:06:59,032
Let me tell you something, sweetheart,
the games are over.

828
01:06:59,199 --> 01:07:01,660
I want you to tell me right now...

829
01:07:02,077 --> 01:07:05,121
why Johnny was making phone calls
from this room.

830
01:07:05,539 --> 01:07:07,374
He was afraid to call from home.

831
01:07:07,457 --> 01:07:08,500
Why?

832
01:07:08,667 --> 01:07:12,337
His stepfather. Johnny knew
some bad things he was doing.

833
01:07:12,671 --> 01:07:15,674
Would you happen to know
where we could find this boy?

834
01:07:15,757 --> 01:07:19,094
His stepfather put him away
at Our Lady Of Angels.

835
01:07:20,762 --> 01:07:24,224
You don't think Deverell would kill
his own stepson, do you?

836
01:07:25,767 --> 01:07:28,687
Right. Dumb question.
Let's get out of here.

837
01:08:26,286 --> 01:08:28,914
- You all right, Johnny?
- Yeah, never been better.

838
01:08:28,997 --> 01:08:31,750
Yeah, we need to ask some questions
about your stepdad.

839
01:08:31,833 --> 01:08:33,210
He's a prick.

840
01:08:34,169 --> 01:08:35,837
Yeah, besides that.

841
01:08:37,297 --> 01:08:39,257
Did your dad kill Dunleavy?

842
01:08:40,550 --> 01:08:43,720
Yeah, I tried to call him,
I tried to warn him, I swear to God.

843
01:08:43,803 --> 01:08:45,972
We know, we know. It's all right.

844
01:08:47,432 --> 01:08:49,976
All right, everybody just relax. Police.

845
01:08:50,310 --> 01:08:51,603
Why'd he do it?

846
01:08:51,770 --> 01:08:54,731
Okay, he had Donald kill his translator...

847
01:08:56,107 --> 01:09:00,570
because she knew that my father was
smugglin' in some bad shit from Russia.

848
01:09:01,446 --> 01:09:03,365
And I found out about it.

849
01:09:03,657 --> 01:09:07,160
So, he got all freaked out,
and thought I told Dr. Dunleavy.

850
01:09:07,661 --> 01:09:10,372
So he had Donald kill him and his wife...

851
01:09:10,455 --> 01:09:12,958
and made it look
like the serial killer did it.

852
01:09:13,041 --> 01:09:14,459
Who was helpin' him?

853
01:09:14,543 --> 01:09:16,127
Some little guy.

854
01:09:17,504 --> 01:09:19,005
Southern accent....

855
01:09:20,173 --> 01:09:22,133
- Smith.
- Yeah, the government guy.

856
01:09:22,217 --> 01:09:23,677
Who's Smith?

857
01:09:24,052 --> 01:09:26,096
You're about to find out.

858
01:09:26,179 --> 01:09:28,265
Sister, take this boy
and keep an eye on him.

859
01:09:28,348 --> 01:09:30,642
Don't let anything happen to him.
Don't leave him alone.

860
01:09:30,725 --> 01:09:33,812
Yes, of course.
I'll take care of you, Johnny. Come.

861
01:09:40,735 --> 01:09:42,237
See you later, Joe.

862
01:10:07,345 --> 01:10:08,597
How you doin'?

863
01:10:10,849 --> 01:10:13,101
Jack, what a pleasant surprise...

864
01:10:18,148 --> 01:10:20,942
You know, in most states in this country...

865
01:10:21,151 --> 01:10:24,821
kidnapping is still a no-no.
Hell, we don't even do it anymore.

866
01:10:24,905 --> 01:10:27,407
Do me a favor. Spare me the drama and...

867
01:10:27,574 --> 01:10:30,285
tell me a story.
What's Deverell smuggling?

868
01:10:31,244 --> 01:10:33,205
I have no idea what you're talking about.

869
01:10:33,288 --> 01:10:34,247
Really?

870
01:10:36,416 --> 01:10:38,919
Goddamn, Jack! What are you doin', man?

871
01:10:39,961 --> 01:10:44,299
Deverell's killed four people to hide
something, and I want to find out what.

872
01:10:44,549 --> 01:10:46,593
You're a fuckin' psycho.

873
01:10:47,719 --> 01:10:50,138
I don't know what the hell
he's talkin' about.

874
01:10:50,222 --> 01:10:51,515
Well, you're a cop!

875
01:10:51,598 --> 01:10:53,225
Aren't you gonna help?

876
01:10:53,892 --> 01:10:55,060
Okay.

877
01:10:55,602 --> 01:10:57,729
But I'm a really bad shot.

878
01:10:57,896 --> 01:11:00,482
- Stay out of it.
- I'm just tryin' to help.

879
01:11:01,316 --> 01:11:03,527
Kill me if you like, you son of a bitch.

880
01:11:03,610 --> 01:11:06,363
I still have no idea
what you're talkin' about.

881
01:11:07,906 --> 01:11:11,076
Jack, I know we've had some harsh words
in the past....

882
01:11:19,793 --> 01:11:22,420
- I tell you I do not know...
- Okay....

883
01:11:28,426 --> 01:11:31,012
I need that hand. Jack, I need that hand.

884
01:11:31,429 --> 01:11:33,932
You know I will. Right about....

885
01:11:34,307 --> 01:11:36,601
All right! Time! Game over!

886
01:11:51,283 --> 01:11:53,160
God I miss you, Jack.

887
01:11:55,036 --> 01:11:58,331
So many young men today
just won't go that extra mile.

888
01:11:59,374 --> 01:12:02,252
I miss you too, Smith. Now, what is it?

889
01:12:03,044 --> 01:12:04,546
Deverell is smugglin'...

890
01:12:04,629 --> 01:12:06,464
chemical weapons in from Russia.

891
01:12:06,548 --> 01:12:10,886
I made the contacts for him. The deal's
being brokered by the Russian Mafia.

892
01:12:12,345 --> 01:12:15,640
Would one of you gentlemen mind
callin' me an ambulance?

893
01:12:15,807 --> 01:12:17,976
So, what's he doin' with this stuff?

894
01:12:18,059 --> 01:12:21,521
Deal's bein' done tomorrow.
Some welfare hotel downtown.

895
01:12:21,855 --> 01:12:24,691
He's sellin' it to a bunch
of Serbian freedom fighters.

896
01:12:24,774 --> 01:12:26,318
You mean terrorists.

897
01:12:26,651 --> 01:12:28,904
Semantics. You say tomato...

898
01:12:29,529 --> 01:12:32,616
No, motherfucker, I didn't say, "tomato".
I said, "terrorists".

899
01:12:32,699 --> 01:12:33,909
You work for the government.

900
01:12:33,992 --> 01:12:36,620
Why would you, of all people,
help Deverell?

901
01:12:39,039 --> 01:12:41,958
To get rich, son. To get rich, why else?

902
01:12:42,542 --> 01:12:43,835
You got that?

903
01:12:44,503 --> 01:12:46,213
Yeah, I got that.

904
01:12:49,382 --> 01:12:51,927
Well, aren't you the grown-up spy?

905
01:12:54,179 --> 01:12:55,847
What do you want?

906
01:12:56,223 --> 01:12:59,976
I want you and your friends
to leave me alone. Forget that I exist.

907
01:13:00,060 --> 01:13:01,228
I already have.

908
01:13:01,311 --> 01:13:02,854
Don't make me come back and kill you.

909
01:13:02,938 --> 01:13:04,272
- I won't.
- Good.

910
01:13:10,737 --> 01:13:14,074
Gentlemen, we must not forget
the little matter...

911
01:13:15,242 --> 01:13:17,869
of the ambulance.
- I only shot you in one foot.

912
01:13:17,953 --> 01:13:19,830
Hobble to a hospital.

913
01:13:32,300 --> 01:13:36,513
Well, safe to assume, folks,
that the rainiest winter in memory is over.

914
01:13:36,596 --> 01:13:41,059
Sunny and dry weather for tomorrow
and for the entire five-day period.

915
01:13:41,268 --> 01:13:44,729
Everything we could hope for
in this part of the country....

916
01:13:45,730 --> 01:13:48,900
Deverell is smugglin' chemical weapons in
from Russia.

917
01:13:49,609 --> 01:13:52,195
The deal's bein' brokered
by the Russian Mafia.

918
01:13:52,279 --> 01:13:54,447
- Who is this?
- So, how's that, asshole?

919
01:13:54,531 --> 01:13:57,701
I know you're friends with everyone
from the postman to the President...

920
01:13:57,784 --> 01:14:00,245
but no one will touch you
with a ten-foot pole...

921
01:14:00,328 --> 01:14:01,997
when this shit gets out. Understand?

922
01:14:02,080 --> 01:14:03,665
Detective Cole.

923
01:14:04,291 --> 01:14:06,960
You are persistent, I'll give you that.

924
01:14:07,043 --> 01:14:10,088
Looks like I got somethin' you want,
you got somethin' I want.

925
01:14:10,172 --> 01:14:12,424
- What might that be?
- Donald.

926
01:14:12,799 --> 01:14:14,885
Donald's your triggerman, isn't he?

927
01:14:14,968 --> 01:14:15,927
I'm listening.

928
01:14:16,011 --> 01:14:17,846
I want him, not you.

929
01:14:17,929 --> 01:14:20,765
Deliver him to me with a nice bow
and the murder weapon.

930
01:14:20,849 --> 01:14:22,559
I'll take it from there.

931
01:14:22,642 --> 01:14:26,730
You take the tape...my name
gets clean...your name stays clean.

932
01:14:27,314 --> 01:14:29,232
Everybody's happy, how's that?

933
01:14:29,316 --> 01:14:30,484
Done.

934
01:14:31,610 --> 01:14:33,361
Why don't you meet me tomorrow?

935
01:14:33,445 --> 01:14:37,032
I'm doing a little business at a place
called the Ovington Arms, downtown.

936
01:14:37,115 --> 01:14:40,118
Apartment D-14.
Would 10:00 be good for you?

937
01:14:47,000 --> 01:14:48,919
Why does this gotta be so complicated?

938
01:14:49,002 --> 01:14:51,129
This isn't complicated.
It's nothing but a game.

939
01:14:51,213 --> 01:14:53,256
Reminds me of an old Persian tactician...

940
01:14:53,340 --> 01:14:56,301
trying to teach his young troops strategy.

941
01:14:56,551 --> 01:14:58,720
That, later on, came to be known as chess.

942
01:14:58,804 --> 01:15:00,597
So, we're gonna bore 'em to death now?

943
01:15:00,680 --> 01:15:03,767
Young warriors used to like
to fight head-on.

944
01:15:04,142 --> 01:15:06,394
Old warriors like to wait...

945
01:15:06,853 --> 01:15:10,899
let their opponents expose the board,
work themselves into a corner....

946
01:15:10,982 --> 01:15:13,485
Time to go. Sun Tzu, The Art of War.

947
01:15:14,069 --> 01:15:16,822
Sun Tzu. Just keeps gettin' stranger.

948
01:15:22,077 --> 01:15:23,495
Donald's your triggerman, isn't he?

949
01:15:23,578 --> 01:15:24,496
I'm listening.

950
01:15:24,579 --> 01:15:26,206
I want him, not you.

951
01:15:26,373 --> 01:15:29,251
Deliver him to me with a nice bow
and the murder weapon.

952
01:15:29,334 --> 01:15:30,752
I'll take it from there.

953
01:15:30,836 --> 01:15:33,547
Take the tape...my name gets clean...

954
01:15:34,089 --> 01:15:37,717
your name stays clean.
Everybody's happy, how's that?

955
01:15:38,510 --> 01:15:39,427
Done.

956
01:15:41,346 --> 01:15:44,474
Guess your ass just got sold
down the river, shithead.

957
01:16:13,795 --> 01:16:16,173
This won't take long. Just a quick pick up.

958
01:16:16,256 --> 01:16:17,716
I'm sure it won't.

959
01:17:25,075 --> 01:17:26,493
Shabby, but chic.

960
01:17:36,086 --> 01:17:38,088
Either we're a little early...

961
01:17:38,171 --> 01:17:40,382
or our hosts are a little late.

962
01:17:48,098 --> 01:17:50,267
What the hell is going on, Donald?

963
01:17:51,184 --> 01:17:52,394
You tell me.

964
01:17:54,896 --> 01:17:59,151
You think you're gonna hand me over
to Cole. Bad move, fruitcake.

965
01:18:00,485 --> 01:18:02,904
I don't know what you're talking about.

966
01:18:06,825 --> 01:18:08,326
You'll never get out of here.

967
01:18:08,410 --> 01:18:10,495
No, this is my show from now on.

968
01:18:18,336 --> 01:18:20,422
Positively Shakespearean.

969
01:18:21,673 --> 01:18:22,716
"To be...

970
01:18:23,508 --> 01:18:24,259
"...or not to be!"

971
01:18:24,676 --> 01:18:25,594
Time to go.

972
01:18:25,677 --> 01:18:28,555
Wait. We don't know how many guys are
in there.

973
01:18:28,638 --> 01:18:31,933
What do you want me to do?
Wait till they all kill each other?

974
01:18:32,017 --> 01:18:33,894
If the old warriors are patient and...

975
01:18:33,977 --> 01:18:36,271
all the young warriors,
they kill each other and...

976
01:18:36,354 --> 01:18:37,772
that's how we get to be old.

977
01:18:37,856 --> 01:18:39,566
I like that plan too. You listened well.

978
01:18:39,649 --> 01:18:41,401
That's what I told you in the bar.

979
